---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/layout/PageHeader.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Mythic GME Apps"
  description="Terms of Service for Mythic GME Apps: license, purchases and refunds, acceptable use, disclaimers, and limitations of liability."
  canonicalPath="/terms/"
  alternatePath="/pt/terms/"
  mainClass="legal-main"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="Clear terms for fair use"
    description="License terms, purchases and refunds, acceptable use, and limitations. Last updated: May 28, 2026"
    accent="Legal"
    layout="left"
    icon="fa-solid fa-gavel"
    visualElement="shapes"
    colorScheme="primary"
  />

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="terms-body">
    <div class="container legal-container">
      <header class="section-head" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="accent-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="badge-text">Legal</span>
      </header>
      <h2 id="terms-body" class="section-title">Use the apps with confidence</h2>
      <p class="legal-summary">
        These terms explain the rules for using the Mythic GME apps, the license relationship behind them, platform
        purchases, refunds, and third-party services.
      </p>
      <article class="legal-article">
        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-acceptance">
          <h2 id="terms-acceptance">1) Agreement to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Mythic GME apps and website operated by
            <strong>Jason Holt Digital LLC</strong> ("JHD", "we", "us", or "our"). By downloading, installing, accessing,
            or using the apps or website, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the apps or website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-products">
          <h2 id="terms-products">2) Products Covered</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Mythic GME Mobile</strong> — iPhone, iPad, Android, and Fire tablets</li>
            <li><strong>Mythic GME Digital</strong> — Windows, macOS, and Linux</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <em>Mythic Game Master Emulator 2nd Edition</em> and related names, text, tables, and trademarks are owned
            by Word Mill Creative LLC and used under license. JHD develops the officially licensed digital companion
            apps.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-license">
          <h2 id="terms-license">3) License and Use</h2>
          <p>
            Subject to these Terms, JHD grants you a limited, non‑exclusive, non‑transferable, revocable license to install and use
            the apps for personal, non‑commercial tabletop roleplaying. You may not copy, distribute, sell,
            sublicense, modify, reverse engineer, or create derivative works from the apps except as permitted by law.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Official content:</strong> Licensed Mythic text, tables, and other included reference material are for in‑app use only. Do not extract, copy, redistribute, or republish them outside the apps except where law allows.</li>
            <li><strong>User content:</strong> Your journals, scenes, notes, custom tables, and other original play content remain yours. That content is stored locally unless you choose to export, share, sync, or send it in a support request.</li>
            <li><strong>Prohibited use:</strong> No unlawful, infringing, or automated scraping activities.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-purchases">
          <h2 id="terms-purchases">4) Purchases and Taxes</h2>
          <p>
            The Mythic GME apps do not use subscriptions. Pricing and availability may vary by platform, region, and
            store.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Mobile Expanded Features:</strong> Apple App Store, Google Play, and Amazon Appstore sell a one-time Expanded Features unlock for Mythic GME Mobile.</li>
            <li><strong>Desktop purchases:</strong> Microsoft Store and itch.io sell Mythic GME Digital as a one-time purchase.</li>
            <li><strong>Taxes/VAT:</strong> Taxes, VAT, currency conversion, receipts, and payment processing are handled by the store or payment provider where required.</li>
            <li><strong>Delivery:</strong> Purchased access is delivered after the store or payment provider confirms the purchase.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-refunds">
          <h2 id="terms-refunds">5) Refunds</h2>
          <p>
            Refunds are handled by the store or payment provider that processed the purchase. JHD cannot guarantee a
            refund or override a store's refund decision, but you can contact me if you need help finding the right
            process.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Apple App Store:</strong> Request at <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reportaproblem.apple.com</a></li>
            <li><strong>Google Play:</strong> Follow <a href="https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/15574908" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Play's refund process</a></li>
            <li><strong>Amazon Appstore:</strong> Contact Amazon customer service through <a href="https://developer.amazon.com/docs/in-app-purchasing/iap-faqs.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the process described by Amazon</a></li>
            <li><strong>Microsoft Store:</strong> Follow <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-US/accounts-billing/subscriptions/get-a-refund-for-apps-and-games-purchased-from-microsoft-store" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft's refund process for apps and games</a></li>
            <li><strong>itch.io:</strong> Contact itch.io support or use the refund process described in <a href="https://itch.io/docs/legal/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">itch.io's terms</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-third-party">
          <h2 id="terms-third-party">6) Third‑Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            The apps use third-party services for store distribution, purchases, optional analytics, diagnostics, and
            support paths as described in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. No advertising SDKs are used.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-disclaimer">
          <h2 id="terms-disclaimer">7) Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>
            THE APPS AND WEBSITE ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED,
            INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND
            NON‑INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE APPS WILL BE ERROR‑FREE OR UNINTERRUPTED.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section" aria-labelledby="terms-liability">
